						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the compound of the Jaina basadi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Āhavamalla [Sōmēśvara I] 1047 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Mentions the rule of Chālukya Āhavamalla and records the gift of the income from the levy on salt for the up keep of the tank Piriyakere by the six Seṭṭis and one hundred-and-twenty <hi rend="italic">nagara [nakhara]</hi> probably of Koḷḷipāke.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 9(6)9 Sarvajit, Kārttika śu. 15 Monday corresponding to 1047 A.D., November 5, Thursday.</p>						

						</summary>
